Caecilius Metellus Scipio, a descendant of Nasica, called the attention of Atticus to what he considered Cicero’s error, as he himself had set up a gilded eques· trian statue in honor of his ances- , tor (cf. quas... posuit), to say nothing of the ancient statue of Serapion already standing near the temple of Ops. But the statue standing near the temple of Ops has causon inscribed upon it, and cannot therefore represent Sera- pion, who never held that office.
